<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
  <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Publish Your OOS</h1>
  <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-8">Capture your AI coordination intelligence in a structured format. Claims with confidence ratings, evidence types, and failure modes.</p>

  <form id="publish-form">
    <!-- Step 1: Template -->
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-4">1. Choose Your Template</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <label class="border rounded-lg p-4 cursor-pointer hover:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:bg-otp-50">
          <input type="radio" name="template" value="agent_army" class="sr-only" checked>
          <div class="font-medium text-sm mb-1">Agent Army</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-500">For orgs with named AI agents that have defined roles and coordinate with each other.</div>
        </label>
        <label class="border rounded-lg p-4 cursor-pointer hover:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:bg-otp-50">
          <input type="radio" name="template" value="value_chain" class="sr-only">
          <div class="font-medium text-sm mb-1">Value Chain</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-500">For orgs that map AI capabilities to their business process flow.</div>
        </label>
        <label class="border rounded-lg p-4 cursor-pointer hover:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:bg-otp-50">
          <input type="radio" name="template" value="org_chart" class="sr-only">
          <div class="font-medium text-sm mb-1">Org Chart</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-500">For orgs that map AI capabilities to departments and functions.</div>
        </label>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 2: Content -->
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border mb-6">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
        <h2 class="font-semibold">2. Paste Your OOS Content</h2>
        <button type="button" onclick="loadExample()" class="text-xs text-otp-500 hover:underline">Load Example</button>
      </div>
      <textarea id="oos-content" name="rawContent" rows="30"
        class="w-full font-mono text-sm border rounded-lg p-4 focus:border-otp-500 focus:ring-1 focus:ring-otp-500"
        placeholder="Paste your OOS markdown here. Include YAML frontmatter between --- delimiters, then your sections and claims.

Example claim format:

**[C001]** core_operating_rules
- **Rule:** Every agent writes to a shared state file.
- **Why:** Direct access creates race conditions.
- **Failure mode:** Agents get conflicting data.
- **Confidence:** HIGH
- **Evidence:** MEASURED_RESULT
- **Scope:** All agents."></textarea>
      <div class="flex justify-between mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400">
        <span id="word-count">0 words (need 1800-3000)</span>
        <span id="claim-count">0 claims detected</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 3: Validate & Preview -->
    <div class="flex gap-3">
      <button type="button" onclick="validateOOS()" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gray-100 border rounded-lg font-medium text-sm hover:bg-gray-200">
        Validate
      </button>
      <button type="button" onclick="publishOOS()" class="px-6 py-3 bg-otp-500 text-white rounded-lg font-medium text-sm hover:bg-otp-400">
        Validate & Publish
      </button>
    </div>

    <!-- Validation Results -->
    <div id="validation-results" class="mt-6 hidden">
      <div id="validation-errors" class="hidden">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-600 mb-2">Errors (must fix before publishing)</h3>
        <div id="error-list" class="space-y-2"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="validation-warnings" class="hidden mt-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-yellow-600 mb-2">Warnings (recommended to fix)</h3>
        <div id="warning-list" class="space-y-2"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="pii-flags" class="hidden mt-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-600 mb-2">PII Detected (must resolve)</h3>
        <div id="pii-list" class="space-y-2"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="validation-success" class="hidden mt-4">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 p-4 rounded-lg text-green-800">
          OOS published successfully! <a id="published-link" href="#" class="underline">View your published OOS</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </form>
</div>

<script>
const textarea = document.getElementById('oos-content');

textarea.addEventListener('input', () => {
  const text = textarea.value;

  // Word count (rough -- content after frontmatter)
  const contentMatch = text.match(/^---[\s\S]*?---\n([\s\S]*)$/);
  const content = contentMatch ? contentMatch[1] : text;
  const words = content.trim().split(/\s+/).filter(w => w.length > 0).length;
  document.getElementById('word-count').textContent =
    `${words} words ${words < 1800 ? '(need ' + (1800 - words) + ' more)' : words > 3000 ? '(over by ' + (words - 3000) + ')' : '(good)'}`;

  // Claim count
  const claimMatches = text.match(/\*\*\[C\d+\]\*\*/g);
  const claimCount = claimMatches ? claimMatches.length : 0;
  document.getElementById('claim-count').textContent =
    `${claimCount} claims detected ${claimCount < 10 ? '(need at least 10)' : '(good)'}`;
});

function handleAuthError(data, status) {
  if (status === 401) {
    if (window.__clerk) {
      window.__clerk.openSignIn({ redirectUrl: '/publish' });
    } else {
      alert('Please sign in to publish.');
    }
    return true;
  }
  if (data.error?.code === 'ORG_NOT_FOUND') {
    window.location.href = '/dashboard';
    return true;
  }
  return false;
}

async function validateOOS() {
  const template = document.querySelector('input[name="template"]:checked').value;
  const rawContent = textarea.value;

  try {
    const resp = await fetch('/api/v1/oos', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ template, rawContent }),
    });
    const data = await resp.json();
    if (handleAuthError(data, resp.status)) return;
    showValidation(data);
  } catch (e) {
    alert('Failed to validate. Check your content format.');
  }
}

async function publishOOS() {
  const template = document.querySelector('input[name="template"]:checked').value;
  const rawContent = textarea.value;

  try {
    // Create draft
    const createResp = await fetch('/api/v1/oos', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ template, rawContent }),
    });
    const createData = await createResp.json();
    if (handleAuthError(createData, createResp.status)) return;

    if (createData.validation && !createData.validation.valid) {
      showValidation(createData);
      return;
    }

    // Publish
    const publishResp = await fetch(`/api/v1/oos/${createData.oosFile.id}/publish`, {
      method: 'POST',
    });
    const publishData = await publishResp.json();
    if (handleAuthError(publishData, publishResp.status)) return;

    if (publishData.error) {
      showValidation(publishData);
      return;
    }

    // Success
    document.getElementById('validation-results').classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('validation-success').classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('published-link').href = `/oos/${createData.oosFile.id}`;

  } catch (e) {
    alert('Failed to publish. Check your content and try again.');
  }
}

function showValidation(data) {
  const container = document.getElementById('validation-results');
  container.classList.remove('hidden');

  const errorDiv = document.getElementById('validation-errors');
  const warningDiv = document.getElementById('validation-warnings');
  const piiDiv = document.getElementById('pii-flags');

  errorDiv.classList.add('hidden');
  warningDiv.classList.add('hidden');
  piiDiv.classList.add('hidden');

  if (data.error?.details || (data.validation?.errors && data.validation.errors.length > 0)) {
    errorDiv.classList.remove('hidden');
    const errors = data.error?.details || data.validation?.errors || [];
    document.getElementById('error-list').innerHTML = errors.map(e =>
      `<div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 p-3 rounded text-sm text-red-800">${e.message || e.issue || JSON.stringify(e)}</div>`
    ).join('');
  }

  if (data.validation?.warnings && data.validation.warnings.length > 0) {
    warningDiv.classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('warning-list').innerHTML = data.validation.warnings.map(w =>
      `<div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 p-3 rounded text-sm text-yellow-800">${w.message}</div>`
    ).join('');
  }

  if (data.piiFlags && data.piiFlags.length > 0) {
    piiDiv.classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('pii-list').innerHTML = data.piiFlags.map(f =>
      `<div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 p-3 rounded text-sm text-red-800">
        <strong>${f.type}:</strong> "${f.text}" found in ${f.location}. <em>${f.suggestion}</em>
      </div>`
    ).join('');
  }
}

function loadExample() {
  textarea.value = `---
oos_version: "1.0"
org_pseudonym: "My AI Team"
industry: "technology"
org_size: "small"
template: "agent_army"
agent_count: 3
platforms:
  - "claude"
generated_at: "${new Date().toISOString()}"
version: 1
parent_version: null
word_count: 1900
claim_count: 12
confidence_distribution:
  high: 4
  medium: 5
  low: 3
evidence_distribution:
  human_defined_rule: 3
  observed_once: 2
  observed_repeatedly: 3
  measured_result: 2
  inference: 1
  speculation: 1
---

## Purpose

A small technology team running 3 AI agents for content creation, research, and project management. This OOS captures coordination patterns discovered over 3 months of production use.

## Prime Directives

1. No agent sends external content without human approval.
2. Every agent writes to its own shared state file.
3. Human decision-maker has final authority on all strategic decisions.

## System Identity

A technology organization using AI agents to augment a small team. Agents handle repetitive operational tasks so humans focus on strategy, relationships, and creative decisions.

**[C001]** core_operating_rules
- **Rule:** Each agent writes to its own shared state file. No agent modifies another agent's state.
- **Why:** Prevents data corruption from concurrent writes.
- **Failure mode:** Two agents write to the same file. One update is lost. State becomes inconsistent.
- **Confidence:** HIGH
- **Evidence:** MEASURED_RESULT
- **Scope:** All agents. Each agent has exactly one state file it owns.

**[C002]** core_operating_rules
- **Rule:** External communications require human approval before sending.
- **Why:** AI-generated content can be tonally wrong or factually incorrect.
- **Failure mode:** Agent sends email with incorrect information. Recipient loses trust.
- **Confidence:** HIGH
- **Evidence:** HUMAN_DEFINED_RULE
- **Scope:** All external emails, messages, and published content.

**[C003]** core_operating_rules
- **Rule:** Research agent summarizes findings but does not make recommendations.
- **Why:** Recommendations without business context led to irrelevant suggestions.
- **Failure mode:** Agent recommends action that conflicts with current business priorities.
- **Confidence:** HIGH
- **Evidence:** OBSERVED_REPEATEDLY
- **Scope:** Research and analysis functions only.

**[C004]** core_operating_rules
- **Rule:** All agent actions are logged to an audit trail.
- **Why:** Without logs, debugging agent errors takes hours instead of minutes.
- **Failure mode:** Agent makes error. No log. Team cannot determine what happened.
- **Confidence:** HIGH
- **Evidence:** MEASURED_RESULT
- **Scope:** All agents, all actions.

**[C005]** agent_roles_and_authority
- **Rule:** Content agent has semi-autonomous authority. It drafts but never publishes.
- **Why:** Content quality requires human judgment for tone and accuracy.
- **Failure mode:** Auto-published content contains errors. Public trust damaged.
- **Confidence:** MEDIUM
- **Evidence:** OBSERVED_ONCE
- **Scope:** Content creation workflow.

**[C006]** agent_roles_and_authority
- **Rule:** Research agent operates autonomously for data gathering but escalates analysis to humans.
- **Why:** Data gathering is safe to automate. Interpretation requires context.
- **Failure mode:** Agent misinterprets data and propagates incorrect analysis.
- **Confidence:** MEDIUM
- **Evidence:** OBSERVED_REPEATEDLY
- **Scope:** Research and analysis tasks.

**[C007]** agent_roles_and_authority
- **Rule:** Project management agent tracks deadlines but does not reassign work.
- **Why:** Work assignment requires understanding of team capacity and priorities that the agent lacks.
- **Failure mode:** Agent reassigns work to someone already overloaded. Deadline missed.
- **Confidence:** MEDIUM
- **Evidence:** INFERENCE
- **Scope:** Project tracking functions.

**[C008]** coordination_patterns
- **Rule:** Agents coordinate through shared state files, not direct messaging.
- **Why:** Direct messaging creates hidden dependencies and unauditable coordination.
- **Failure mode:** Agent-to-agent message not logged. Coordination failure is invisible.
- **Confidence:** MEDIUM
- **Evidence:** OBSERVED_REPEATEDLY
- **Scope:** All multi-agent coordination.

**[C009]** failure_patterns
- **Rule:** We tried giving the content agent access to publish directly. Quality dropped immediately.
- **Why:** The agent optimized for speed over accuracy when it could publish without review.
- **Failure mode:** Three blog posts published with factual errors in one week.
- **Confidence:** HIGH
- **Evidence:** OBSERVED_ONCE
- **Scope:** Content publishing. Reverted to human-approval model.

**[C010]** failure_patterns
- **Rule:** Single shared state file for all agents caused data corruption within the first week.
- **Why:** Concurrent writes from multiple agents created race conditions.
- **Failure mode:** State file contained mixed data from two agents. Required manual cleanup.
- **Confidence:** MEDIUM
- **Evidence:** MEASURED_RESULT
- **Scope:** Shared state architecture. Resolved by per-agent files.

**[C011]** human_ai_boundary_conditions
- **Rule:** Financial commitments and pricing decisions require human approval.
- **Why:** Financial decisions have legal and relationship implications AI cannot assess.
- **Failure mode:** Agent agrees to terms that violate margin requirements.
- **Confidence:** LOW
- **Evidence:** SPECULATION
- **Scope:** All financial decisions. Precautionary rule.

**[C012]** human_ai_boundary_conditions
- **Rule:** The founder has unlimited override authority over all agents at any time.
- **Why:** A human must always be able to stop any AI action immediately.
- **Failure mode:** No override mechanism exists. Harmful AI action cannot be stopped.
- **Confidence:** MEDIUM
- **Evidence:** HUMAN_DEFINED_RULE
- **Scope:** All agents. Non-negotiable.

## Confidence Map

| Confidence | Count |
|---|---|
| HIGH | 4 |
| MEDIUM | 5 |
| LOW | 3 |

## Merge Protocol

Import claims at LOW confidence. Do not auto-merge contradictions. Preserve provenance.

## Update Protocol

Review every 90 days. Flag stale claims. Update confidence when evidence strengthens.

## Summary

1. Per-agent shared state files prevent data corruption.
2. External communications always require human approval.
3. Research summarizes but does not recommend.
4. Audit trails on every action enable fast debugging.
5. Direct publishing access for content agents degrades quality.
6. Single shared state files cause corruption -- use per-agent files.
7. Financial decisions are human-only.
8. Founder has unlimited override authority.
`;
  textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input'));
}
</script>
